Hey guys, thanks for your patience over the weekend. We are addressing these issues ASAP today. 

Here's our DTAO upgrade plan, summarized. We hope to have these changes implemented by the end of the week. I will be focusing on this full time and all other projects are now on the back burner for me:

## 1. Switching data providers for one that is more reliable
## 2. Adding several new bet types, when the data is available.  (point spread, over/under, etc)
## 3. Emissions control.
- This is a solution that other subnets have implemented in order to decrease sell pressure. Essentially, the combined pressure from miners, validators, and root selling are resulting in fewer rewards for everyone.
- We have to take a hard look at which miners are actually providing us with useful data, and **only** reward those ones. What this means is, we will be decreasing the overall reward pool by about 50%, and directing those rewards to a key which we will recycle later (or potentially use for other direct subnet "investment", pending general approval from all participants) . Miners must demonstrate positive ROI over a solid time frame to receive reward, so it will mostly be miners in tier 3,4,5 that continue to receive rewards.
- We aren't thrilled about this necessity either, and wish there was a better way to accomplish this. But we see it as a short term solution until root pressure diminishes.
- We expect that the miners in the higher tiers will not see a significant change in their rewards, as they are already providing value for us.
- We are open to further discussion on this subject, but please remember to respect the server rules here and tread lightly.
## 4. User facing product and revenue stream
- check out our beta product here - https://pickpro.ai/
- this product will be live on web, as well as mobile app versions. We will be using this to monetize subnet outputs and direct revenue back into the subnet.

Ok, so just to reiterate and expand on our plan in more detail:

two major features that we plan to release ASAP:

1. emissions control/vesting. 

- miners with a non-positive ROI for tiers 3 and above will be demoted immediately.

- tiers 1 & 2 will no longer reward the bottom 50% of total keys. Effectively this means the majority of tier 1 and 2 will not receive significant incentive.

- the immunity period will slightly increase to account for this increase in difficulty

- the remaining incentive will be directed to a hotkey our team controls, to be fully recycled once a chain-level emissions control feature is released. Alternatively, we could use this to fund other subnet wide improvements (but we don't have any in mind yet. We will be fully transparent and allow open discussion and contribution before any funds are moved)

-  we will introduce a "vesting" bonus for miners that hold a portion of their rewards. We will release details on this soon, but essentially, if you keep a portion of your rewards staked for defined time steps, you will receive an incentive multiplier to your final weight. This is a strong signal and bonus for miners that are here for the long term success of the subnet, and not just here to earn and dump. 

- please feel free to share thoughts, feedback, etc as we move to implementing these features

- As the first step in our DTAO overhaul, we've just dramatically changed the incentive curve to more heavily reward top performers. It should update across all validators shortly.

- After feedback and analysis from other subnets, we have decided NOT to reduce overall miner emission by using a "freeze/recycle" key

Its not likely due to problems with the validators, just latency. But here's an example:

Validators query our API for game data updates every 1-5 min and update odds/game data if changes are detected.

A miner submits a prediction with "old" odds in the middle of this update process

The validator receives the prediction, but takes the newly updated odds instead of the old one .

(if we honored any odds submitted instead of relying on ground truth, it opens up possible cheating avenues)

So our new system will be two-fold - we'll track odds history, so that we can honor submissions on older odds if they fall within a certain time frame (say 1-3 min)

Additionally, miners/validators will communicate with a pub/sub websocket model - so as soon as a prediction is submitted on a miner locally, it gets published to all validators and processed immediately.  Conversely, validators will also publish game data updates so they are available immediately to miners, instead of using the periodic querying that most bittensor subnets use
